The paper discusses the use of robot arms and their redundancy to find shorter paths, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The experiment involves pruning grape vines, which could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if image processing is involved. The proposed approach involves using the extra goal configurations to find higher quality paths, which could involve machine learning (cs.AI) or optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the approach aims to reduce execution times, which could involve control systems (cs.SY).
